cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG

This paper deals with maximizing influence spread in social networks, which is a problem related to social networks and their analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves formulating an objective function and proposing algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves studying the problem of determining an optimal budget-split and delay between the two phases, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the properties of the objective function, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves studying the effects of selecting and activating seed nodes, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Retrieval).
